salmonella is the most common (but not only) issue with uncooked egg product.<br />
<br />
check your local markets for pasteurized fresh eggs - using the in-the-shell pasteurized variety should dramatically reduce the risk of salmonella in your homemade mayo.<br />
<br />
do observe the requirements for refrigerated storage, etc. - you can not just leave it sitting at room temps at a picnic for all day . . .</div>
