					<div class="commentheading">On April 15, 2008 at 04:24 PM, bsheitman (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>Fixing a broken emulsion</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">One trick I've heard but haven't tried for fixing a broken emulsion is start a new emulsion with 1 egg yolk and add the oil slowly(apparently slower than you did last time).  Once this emulsion is established you can drizzle the failed batch in and it should thicken.  Due to the additional lecithin from the extra yolk you may want to add more oil(and seasoning) accordingly.</div>
