					<div class="commentheading">On August 08, 2008 at 11:16 PM, ultra (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>runny mayonaise no more</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">I have found that the method or process for making mayonnaise is what makes it work.<br />
When in the past I have obtained runny mayonnaise, usually by pouring the oil too fast, I can fix it by starting again using the runny mayonnaise as I would use the oil.<br />
Put the runny stuff into a jug with a spout,<br />
Use one egg yolk beat until creamy<br />
Then add a bit of the runny mayo VERY SLOWLY, mix with the egg using a mixer, and then add bit more oil, mix again and so on continuously mixing <br />
It should start being emulsified very quickly</div>
